            <q>Page 28, line 25, at end insert&#x2014;</q>
            <q>(6A) In performing his duties under subsections (3) and (6) the Regulator shall seek contributions from the groups of persons set out in subsection (6B) in the order in which they are set out, and shall not seek contributions from persons in a lower group if, in his opinion, persons in a higher group are together capable of furnishing (and likely to furnish) a sufficient total contribution.</q>
            <q>(6B) The groups referred to in subsection (6A) are&#x2014;</q>
            <ol type="a">
            <li>companies owned by or owning the employer in a 100% shareholding relationship,</li>
            <li>companies owned by or owning the employer in a 75% to 100% shareholding relationship,</li>
