      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S5LV0663P0_20040713_GCR_26'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-roger-bootle-wilbraham' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040713_GCR_26' title='Link to this speech by Mr Roger Bootle-Wilbraham' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-roger-bootle-wilbraham" title="Mr Roger Bootle-Wilbraham">Lord Skelmersdale</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            had given notice of his intention to move Amendment No. 118:
            <q>Page 28, line 27, after "period" insert "not exceeding five years</q></p><p>
            The noble Lord said: I do not expect the Minister to respond a jot, a tittle, or even a single word to this amendment. This subject has been covered already and continues to be in the noble Baroness's thinking.
