          <p class='first-para'>
            Yes. In practice anyone who took documents without signing for them would be a fool, because there would be no record of where they had been obtained and there would be no paper trail that would stand up in court if a criminal process were to be pursued. Such a practice is required by the <a href="/acts/police-and-criminal-evidence-act-1984">Police and Criminal Evidence Act</a> Code B and the inspectors would abide by that.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
